###Bouraka Installation:

1. Install python-dev
```bash
sudo apt-get install python-dev 
```
2. Install virtualenv

```bash
sudo apt-get install virtualenv 
virtualenv --no-site-packages pic 
```
pic will be the folder containning the virtual env where bouraka is going to be installed.

3. Then install the requirements
``` bash
pip install -r requirement.txt

python /path/to/manage.py syncdb
python /path/to/manage.py migrate
python /path/to/manage.py collectstatic
```
4. Deployement: 

```bash 
sudo apt-get install apache2 libapache2-mod-wsgi

vi /etc/apache2/apache2.conf
``` 
Append This At The End Of The File
``` bash
  # Include the virtual host configurations:
  Include sites-enabled/
  ServerName localhost
  WSGIPythonPath /pic/bouraka:/pic/lib/python2.7/site-packages

vi /etc/apache2/sites-available/protoinsaclub.tk.conf
<VirtualHost *:80>
        WSGIScriptAlias / /pic/bouraka/pic_site/wsgi.py

        ServerName protoinsaclub.tk
        ServerAlias www.protoinsaclub.tk

        Alias /static/ /pic/bouraka-static/
        Alias /media/ /pic/bouraka-media/


        <Directory /pic/bouraka/pic-site>
                <Files wsgi.py>
                        Order deny,allow
                        Allow from all
                </Files>
        </Directory>
</VirtualHost>

``` 

```bash 
sudo a2ensite protoinsaclub.tk.conf
```

